\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\lang9 INTRODUCTION OF BLOCKCHAIN TECHNOLOGY :\par
Blockchain technology is a decentralized digital ledger system that records transactions across multiple computers in a secure and immutable manner. Each transaction, or "block," is linked to the previous one, forming a "chain" of blocks. This distributed ledger eliminates the need for intermediaries, such as banks, by enabling peer-to-peer transactions. Through cryptographic techniques, transactions on a blockchain are highly secure and transparent, as every participant can view the entire transaction history. This technology finds applications beyond cryptocurrencies, including supply chain management, voting systems, and digital identity verification, promising increased efficiency, transparency, and security across various industries.\par
